1.description: The I2C driver has not been initialised.

2.description: Failed to enable an I2C peripheral.

3.description: Failed to enable a GPIO peripheral. *

4.description: Indicates that no action has been queued for the given device

5.description: Attempted to check the TivaWare error status of an action which is of type NONE.

6.description: Error indicating that a user attempted to read recieved bytes from a device that had sent data.

9.description: Failed to allocate memory for send action.

10.description: Failed to allocate memory for recieve action.

11.description: A new action could not be queued as the maximum number of actions has been reached.

12.description: A new action could not be queued as the maximum number of actions has been reached.

13.description: An unexpected action step index was found while executing an action.

14.description: An unexpected action step index was found while executing an action.

15.description: A master I2C module is busy.

16.description: Failed to acknowledge the address of an I2C device, is the device address correct?

17.description: Failed to acknowledge data sent to the master. The slave could be unresponsive.

18.description: The arbitration of the bus has been lost. This could indicate that a slave is in error.

19.description: An unkown TivaWare library error has occured

21.description: The action cannot be queued as the module (bus) the device is on is already locked by another device.

23.description: There was insufficient memory to increase the size of the event  lists.

24.description: A call to realloc() failed while trying to shrink the lists. This indicates memory corruption.

26.description: Attempted to use the IMU when it wasn't initialised. *

27.description: Attempted to issue an IMU_CMD_NONE to the IMU module.

28.description: There was an error in the EventManager that is preventing the IMU component operating.

32.description: Cannot issue a new command to the IMU since the IMU is not in the WAIT_NEW_COMMAND state. It could either not be initialised or is still finishing another command

33.description: There was an error in the I2C driver.  See the corresponding value of DP.IMU.I2C_ERROR for the root cause.

34.description: Unexpected value of an I2c_ActionStatus return.

1.description: This event indicates that a new action has been requested for the I2C driver to execute.

2.description: Event that indicates when an I2C action has been finished. The user must use I2c_get_device_action_status for their device to determine whether or not their action has finished, or if it was another action.  This event __shall not__ be polled by the user, instead EventManager_is_event_raised must be used. The I2c module will clear the event when all finished actions have been handled.

3.description: Event associated with an event manager error.  This event indicates that an error has occured in the EventManager, and the corresponding error code in the EventManager's DataPool DP.EVENTMANAGER.ERROR_CODE has been set.  Note, if the error arises from already being at the maximum number of events the error code will be set and the corresponding DP.EVENTMANAGER.MAX_EVENTS_REACHED flag will be raised. This event will not be raised.

4.description: New command event.  This event is raised when a new command is issued by a user to the Imu module. It is used to identify when a new command is available to be executed. The user should not raise this event themselves, instead use the Imu_new_command() function.

5.description: IMU gyroscope read command completed successfully.

7.description: IMU magnetometer read command completed successfully.

9.description: IMU temeprature read command completed successfully.

11.description: Event used to signal a state change in the IMU. This is done so that the new state will run it's first function in the next cycle without the system going to sleep.
